
[1]black-cap

   BLACK-CAP, n. [black and cap.] A bird, the Motacilla atricapilla, or
   mock-nightingale; so called from its black crown. It is common in
   Europe.

   1. In cookery, an apple roasted till black, to be served up in a dish
   of boiled custard.
